    {
      "id": "RQ-0031",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Align `machine queue read` runnability output with queue validation state",
      "description": "Principles violated: E (make bugs hard to write), G (least astonishment), J (consistency/integrity). `machine queue read` currently emits runnable task selection and `next_runnable_task_id` even when `queue validate` reports structural invalidity. Why it matters: app/automation surfaces can present a runnable queue while the canonical continuation gate is stalled, creating cross-surface drift and unsafe operator guidance. Minimal fix: validate queue/read payload before reporting runnability, and gate or annotate runnability/next-task fields when structural errors exist.",
      "priority": "high",
      "tags": [
        "maintenance",
        "machine-contract",
        "queue",
        "app-parity"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "crates/ralph/src/cli/machine/common.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/cli/machine/queue.rs",
        "docs/machine-contract.md"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "path: crates/ralph/src/cli/machine/common.rs:84-103 :: `build_queue_read_document` loads queue/done and computes runnability without queue validation.",
        "repro: temp queue with task missing `created_at`, run `/tmp/ralph-scan-target/debug/ralph queue validate` and `/tmp/ralph-scan-target/debug/ralph machine queue read` :: expected queue-read state to reflect invalid/stalled continuation :: actual validate exits 1 (`Missing created_at`) while machine queue read exits 0 and returns `next_runnable_task_id: RQ-0001`",
        "path: docs/machine-contract.md:206 :: `runnability.summary.blocking` is documented as queue/read source of truth for operator blocking state"
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Introduce shared validation-aware queue-read assembly so machine queue-read consumers cannot bypass structural validity checks.",
        "Define machine queue-read behavior for invalid queues (for example explicit invalid/continuation block with null next-runnable).",
        "Add regression tests covering missing required task fields and mismatched queue-read vs queue-validate outputs.",
        "Verify by rerunning the missing-`created_at` repro and confirming queue-read no longer reports runnable next-task when validation fails."
      ],
      "notes": [],
      "request": "scan: queue/load/save correctness, runner subprocess boundaries, macOS app <-> CLI parity, and trust/untrusted-repo safety",
      "created_at": "2026-04-27T00:18:10Z",
